The paper deals with summarizing complex event sequences, which involves data mining and machine learning techniques. The use of the Minimum Description Length principle and the introduction of a new algorithm suggest a focus on database and machine learning techniques (cs.DB and cs.LG). The experiments involve synthetic and real data, which suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of annotated text suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
